## ğŸš€ OpenShift CLI (`oc`) Command Reference

### ğŸ“ Project and Namespace Management
1. `oc new-project <project-name>` â€“ Creates a new project (namespace) with the specified name.
2. `oc project <project-name>` â€“ Switches the current context to the specified project.
3. `oc project` â€“ Lists all projects (namespaces) the user has access to.
4. `oc delete project <project-name>` â€“ Deletes the specified project.

### âš™ï¸ Resource Management
5. `oc get all` â€“ Lists all resources in the current namespace.
6. `oc get <resource-type> <resource-name> -o yaml` â€“ Displays the details of a specific resource in YAML format.
7. `oc apply -f <file.yaml>` â€“ Creates or updates resources based on the YAML or JSON file provided.
8. `oc delete <resource-type> <resource-name>` â€“ Deletes a specific resource.
9. `oc edit <resource-type> <resource-name>` â€“ Edits a resource directly in the terminal.

### ğŸ§± Pods
10. `oc get pods` â€“ Lists all pods in the current namespace.
11. `oc describe pod <pod-name>` â€“ Displays detailed information about a specific pod.
12. `oc logs <pod-name>` â€“ Shows the logs for a specific pod.
13. `oc exec -it <pod-name> -- <command>` â€“ Executes a command inside a running pod.
14. `oc annotate <resource-type> <resource-name> <annotation>` â€“ Adds an annotation to a resource.
15. `oc label <resource-type> <resource-name> <label>` â€“ Adds a label to a resource for easier identification and selection.

### ğŸ“¦ Deployments and ReplicaSets
16. `oc create deployment <deployment-name> --image=<image>` â€“ Creates a new deployment with the specified image.
17. `oc get deployment <deployment-name>` â€“ Shows details about a specific deployment.
18. `oc scale deployment <deployment-name> --replicas=<number>` â€“ Changes the number of replicas of a deployment.
19. `oc rollout status deployment/<deployment-name>` â€“ Displays the status of the latest deployment rollout.
20. `oc rollout undo deployment/<deployment-name>` â€“ Reverts the current deployment to the previous version.

### ğŸŒ Services
21. `oc create service clusterip <service-name> --tcp=8080:80` â€“ Creates a new ClusterIP service.
22. `oc get svc` â€“ Lists all services in the current namespace.
23. `oc expose deployment <deployment-name> --type=ClusterIP --port=8080` â€“ Exposes a deployment as a service.

### ğŸ—‚ ConfigMaps and Secrets
24. `oc create configmap <configmap-name> --from-literal=<key>=<value>` â€“ Creates a ConfigMap.
25. `oc create secret generic <secret-name> --from-literal=<key>=<value>` â€“ Creates a Secret.
26. `oc set env deployment/<deployment-name> <key>=<value>` â€“ Sets an environment variable in a deployment.

### ğŸ’¾ Persistent Volumes and Claims
27. `oc get pv` â€“ Lists all PersistentVolumes.
28. `oc get pvc` â€“ Lists all PersistentVolumeClaims.
29. `oc create -f <pvc-config-file>.yaml` â€“ Creates a PersistentVolumeClaim.

### ğŸ›£ï¸ Networking
30. `oc get network.config.openshift.io/cluster -o yaml` â€“ Displays the cluster network configuration.
31. `oc patch network.config.openshift.io/cluster -p '{"spec":{"clusterNetwork":[{"cidr":"10.128.0.0/14","hostPrefix":23}]}}' --type=merge` â€“ Updates the network CIDR.

### ğŸ–¼ï¸ Image Management
32. `oc image info <image-name>` â€“ Shows image details.
33. `oc tag <image-name> <new-image-name>` â€“ Tags an image with a new name.
34. `oc import-image <image-stream-name> --from=<image-name>` â€“ Imports an image into an image stream.

### ğŸ—ï¸ Build and Image Streams
35. `oc new-build --strategy=Docker --name <image-name> <source-code-location>` â€“ Creates a Docker build config.
36. `oc start-build <image-name>` â€“ Starts a build from an image stream.
37. `oc import-image <image-stream-name> --from=<image-name>` â€“ Imports an image (repeated for emphasis).

### ğŸ”§ Builds and BuildConfigs
38. `oc create bc <build-config-name> --binary --image-stream=python:3.6 --source-secret=mysecret` â€“ Creates a binary build config.
39. `oc start-build <build-config-name>` â€“ Starts a build from the build config.

### ğŸ” Rolling Updates
40. `oc rollout status deployment/<deployment-name>` â€“ Shows deployment rollout status.
41. `oc rollout undo deployment/<deployment-name>` â€“ Reverts to the previous deployment.

### ğŸ§© Troubleshooting
42. `oc logs <pod-name>` â€“ Shows pod logs.
43. `oc describe pod <pod-name>` â€“ Describes a pod in detail.
44. `oc get events` â€“ Lists recent events in the namespace.

### ğŸ” Role-Based Access Control (RBAC)
45. `oc create rolebinding <role-binding-name> --role=admin --user=<username>` â€“ Grants admin role to a user.
46. `oc get clusterrolebindings` â€“ Lists all cluster role bindings.

### ğŸ› ï¸ Operator Management
47. `oc get operators.operators.coreos.com` â€“ Lists all installed operators.
48. `oc adm upgrade` â€“ Initiates a cluster upgrade.

### ğŸ–¥ï¸ MachineSets and Machines
49. `oc get machinesets` â€“ Lists all machine sets.
50. `oc describe machineset <machineset-name>` â€“ Describes a machine set.
